  sectionId (32855)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32855&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) This Act may be called the Prohibition of Benami`
  line `Property Transactions Act, 1988.]`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2***.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sections 3, 5 and 8 shall come into force at once, and the remaining provisions`
  line `of this Act shall be deemed to have come into force on the 19th day of May, 1988.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  line
  line `2. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10- 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (32856)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32856&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[2. Definitions.-- In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(1) Adjudicating Authority means the Adjudicating Authority ^2[referred to in] section 7;`
  line
  line `(2) Administrator means an Income-tax Officer as defined in clause (25) of section 2 of the`
  line `Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961);`
  line
  line `(3) Appellate Tribunal means the Appellate Tribunal established under section 30;`
  line
  line `(4) Approving Authority means an Additional Commissioner or a Joint Commissioner as`
  line `defined in clauses (1C) and (28C) respectively of section 2 of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961);`
  line
  line `(5) attachment means the prohibition of transfer, conversion, disposition or movement of`
  line `property, by an order issued under this Act;`
  line
  line `(6) authority means an authority referred to in sub-section (1) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(7) banking company means a company to which the provisions of the Banking Regulation`
  line `Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), applies and includes any bank or banking institution referred to in section 51`
  line `of that Act;`
  line
  line `(8) benami property means any property which is the subject matter of a benami transaction`
  line `and also includes the proceeds from such property;`
  line
  line `(9) benami transaction means,--`
  line
  line `(A) a transaction or an arrangement--`
  line
  line `(a) where a property is transferred to, or is held by, a person, and the consideration for`
  line `such property has been provided, or paid by, another person; and`
  line
  line `(b) the property is held for the immediate or future benefit, direct or indirect, of the`
  line `person who has provided the consideration,`
  line
  line `except when the property is held by--`
  line
  line `(i) a Karta, or a member of a Hindu undivided family, as the case may be, and the property is`
  line `held for his benefit or benefit of other members in the family and the consideration for such`
  line `property has been provided or paid out of the known sources of the Hindu undivided family;`
  line
  line `(ii) a person standing in a fiduciary capacity for the benefit of another person towards whom`
  line `he stands in such capacity and includes a trustee, executor, partner, director of a company, a`
  line `depository or a participant as an agent of a depository under the Depositories Act, 1996`
  line `(22 of 1996) and any other person as may be notified by the Central Government for this purpose;`
  line
  line `(iii) any person being an individual in the name of his spouse or in the name of any child of`
  line `such individual and the consideration for such property has been provided or paid out of the`
  line `known sources of the individual;`
  line
  line `(iv) any person in the name of his brother or sister or lineal ascendant or descendant, where`
  line `the names of brother or sister or lineal ascendant or descendant and the individual appear as jointowners in any document, and the consideration for such property has been provided or paid out of`
  line `the known sources of the individual; or`
  line
  line `(B) a transaction or an arrangement in respect of a property carried out or made in a fictitious`
  line `name; or`
  line
  line `(C) a transaction or an arrangement in respect of a property where the owner of the property`
  line `is not aware of, or, denies knowledge of, such ownership;`
  line
  line `(D) a transaction or an arrangement in respect of a property where the person providing the`
  line `consideration is not traceable or is fictitious;`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that benami transaction shall not`
  line `include any transaction involving the allowing of possession of any property to be taken or retained in`
  line `part performance of a contract referred to in section 53A of the Transfer of Property`
  line `Act, 1882 (4 of 1882), if, under any law for the time being in force,--`
  line
  line `(i) consideration for such property has been provided by the person to whom possession of`
  line `property has been allowed but the person who has granted possession thereof continues to hold`
  line `ownership of such property;`
  line
  line `(ii) stamp duty on such transaction or arrangement has been paid; and`
  line
  line `(iii) the contract has been registered.`
  line
  line `(10) benamidar means a person or a fictitious person, as the case may be, in whose name the`
  line `benami property is transferred or held and includes a person who lends his name;`
  line
  line `(11) Bench means a Bench of the Adjudicating Authority or the Appellate Tribunal, as the case`
  line `may be;`
  line
  line `(12) beneficial owner means a person, whether his identity is known or not, for whose benefit`
  line `the benami property is held by a benamidar;`
  line
  line `(13) Board means the Central Board of Direct Taxes constituted under the Central Boards of`
  line `Revenue Act, 1963 (54 of 1963);`
  line
  line `(14) director shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (34) of section 2 of the`
  line `Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013);`
  line
  line `(15) executor shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (c) of section 2 of the`
  line `Indian Succession Act, 1925 (39 of 1925);`
  line
  line `(16) fair market value, in relation to a property, means--`
  line
  line `(i) the price that the property would ordinarily fetch on sale in the open market on the date of`
  line `the transaction; and`
  line
  line `(ii) where the price referred to in sub-clause (i) is not ascertainable, such price as may be`
  line `determined in accordance with such manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(17) firm shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in section 4 of the Indian Partnership`
  line `Act, 1932 (9 of 1932) and shall include a limited liability partnership as defined in the Limited`
  line `Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009);`
  line
  line `(18) High Court means--`
  line
  line `(i) the High Court within the jurisdiction of which the aggrieved party ordinarily resides or`
  line `carries on business or personally works for gain; ^2***`
  line
  line `(ii) where the Government is the aggrieved party, the High Court within the jurisdiction of`
  line `which the respondent, or in a case where there are more than one respondent, any of the`
  line `respondents, ordinarily resides or carries on business or personally works for gain; ^3[and]`
  line
  line `^3[(iii) the High Court within the jurisdiction of which the office of the Initiating Officer is`
  line located,--
  line
  line `(a) where the aggrieved party does not ordinarily reside or carry on business or personally`
  line `work for gain in the jurisdiction of any High Court;`
  line
  line `(b) where the Government is the aggrieved party and any of the respondents do not`
  line `ordinarily reside or carry on business or personally work for gain in the jurisdiction of any`
  line `High Court;]`
  line
  line `(19) Initiating Officer means an Assistant Commissioner or a Deputy Commissioner as defined`
  line `in clauses (9A) and (19A) respectively of section 2 of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961);`
  line
  line `(20) Member means the Chairperson or the Member of the Adjudicating Authority or the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(21) notification means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the expression`
  line `notified shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(22) partner shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in section 4 of the Indian Partnership`
  line `Act, 1932 (9 of 1932), and shall include,--`
  line
  line `(a) any person who, being a minor, has been admitted to the benefits of partnership; and`
  line
  line `(b) a partner of a limited liability partnership formed and registered under the Limited`
  line `Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009);`
  line
  line `(23) partnership shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in section 4 of the Indian`
  line `Partnership Act, 1932 (9 of 1932), and shall include a limited liability partnership formed and`
  line `registered under the Limited Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009);`
  line
  line `(24) person shall include--`
  line
  line `(i) an individual;`
  line
  line `(ii) a Hindu undivided family;`
  line
  line `(iii) a company;`
  line
  line `(iv) a firm;`
  line
  line `(v) an association of persons or a body of individuals, whether incorporated or not;`
  line
  line `(vi) every artificial juridical person, not falling under sub-clauses (i) to (v);`
  line
  line `(25) prescribed means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(26) property means assets of any kind, whether movable or immovable, tangible or intangible,`
  line `corporeal or incorporeal and includes any right or interest or legal documents or instruments`
  line `evidencing title to or interest in the property and where the property is capable of conversion into`
  line `some other form, then the property in the converted form and also includes the proceeds from the`
  line property;
  line
  line `(27) public financial institution shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (72) of`
  line `section 2 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013);`
  line
  line `(28) Special Court means a Court of Session designated as Special Court under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 50;`
  line
  line `(29) transfer includes sale, purchase or any other form of transfer of right, title, possession or`
  line lien;
  line
  line `(30) trustee means the trustee as defined in the section 3 of the Indian Trusts Act, 1882 (2 of`
  line `1882);`
  line
  line `(31) words and expressions used herein and not defined in this Act but defined in the Indian`
  line `Trusts Act, 1882 (2 of 1882), the Indian Succession Act, 1925 (39 of 1925), the Indian Partnership`
  line `Act, 1932 (9 of 1932), the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961), the Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of 1996), the Prevention of Money-Laundering Act, 2002 (15 of 2003), the Limited`
  line `Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009) and the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013), shall have the`
  line `same meanings respectively assigned to them in those Acts. ]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for section 2 (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  line
  line `2. The word "and" omitted by Act 8 of 2023, s. 171 (w.e.f. 1-4-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 171, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (32857)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Prohibition of benami transactions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32857&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[3. Prohibition of benami transactions.--(1) No person shall enter into any benami transaction.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(2)] Whoever enters into any benami transaction shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to three years or with fine or with both.`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(3) Whoever enters into any benami transaction on and after the date of commencement of the`
  line `Benami Transactions (Prohibition) Amendment Act, 2016 (43 of 2016) shall, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in sub-section (2), be punishable in accordance with the provisions contained in Chapter VII.]`
  line
  line ^5
  line `* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 43 of 2016, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Omitted by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (3) renumbered as sub-section (2) thereof by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 6, ibid (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  line
  line `5. Omitted by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (32858)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Prohibition of the right to recover property held benami.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Omitted by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32858&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, claim or action to`
  line `enforce any right in respect of any property held benami against the person in whose name the property is`
  line `held or against any other person shall lie by or on behalf of a person claiming to be the real owner of such`
  line property.
  line
  line `(2) No defence based on any right in respect of any property held benami, whether against the person`
  line `in whose name the property is held or against any other person, shall be allowed in any suit, claim or`
  line `action by or on behalf of a person claiming to be the real owner of such property.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (32859)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Property held benami liable to confiscation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for sections 5 and 6 (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32859&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[5. Property held benami liable to confiscation.--Any property, which is subject matter of benami`
  line `transaction, shall be liable to be confiscated by the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (32860)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Prohibition on re-transfer of property by benamidar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for sections 5 and 6 (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32860&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[6. Prohibition on re-transfer of property by benamidar.--(1) No person, being a benamidar shall`
  line `re-transfer the benami property held by him to the beneficial owner or any other person acting on his`
  line behalf.
  line
  line `(2) Where any property is re-transferred in contravention of the provisions of sub-section (1), the`
  line `transaction of such property shall be deemed to be null and void.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-sections (1) and (2) shall not apply to a transfer made in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of section 190 of the Finance Act, 2016 (28 of 2016).]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (32861)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Adjudicating Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 155, for section 7 (w.e.f. 1-7-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32861&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^1[7.Adjudicating Authority.--—The competent authority authorised under sub-section (1) of section 5`
  line `of the Smugglers and Foreign Exchange Manipulators (Forfeiture of Property) Act, 1976 (13 of 1976) shall`
  line `be the Adjudicating Authority to exercise jurisdiction, powers and authority conferred by or under this`
  line Act.]
