obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (32872)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Authorities and jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32872&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `^1[18. Authorities and jurisdiction.--(1) The following shall be the authorities for the purposes of this`
  line `Act, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Initiating Officer;`
  line
  line `(b) the Approving Authority;`
  line
  line `(c) the Administrator; and`
  line
  line `(d) the Adjudicating Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) The authorities shall exercise all or any of the powers and perform all or any of the functions`
  line `conferred on, or, assigned, as the case may be, to it under this Act or in accordance with such rules as may`
  line `be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (32873)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Powers of authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32873&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `^1[19. Powers of authorities.--(1) The authorities shall, for the purposes of this Act, have the same`
  line `powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a`
  line `suit in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) discovery and inspection;`
  line
  line `(b) enforcing the attendance of any person, including any official of a banking company or a`
  line `public financial institution or any other intermediary or reporting entity, and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(c) compelling the production of books of account and other documents;`
  line
  line `(d) issuing commissions;`
  line
  line `(e) receiving evidence on affidavits; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) All the persons summoned under sub-section (1) shall be bound to attend in person or through`
  line `authorised agents, as any authority under this Act may direct, and shall be bound to state the truth upon`
  line `any subject respecting which they are examined or make statements, and produce such documents as may`
  line `be required.`
  line
  line `(3) Every proceeding under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be deemed to be a judicial`
  line `proceeding within the meaning of section 193 and section 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of this Act, any authority under this Act may requisition the service of any police`
  line `officer or of any officer of the Central Government or State Government or of both to assist him for all or`
  line `any of the purposes specified in sub-section (1), and it shall be the duty of every such officer to comply`
  line `with the requisition or direction.`
  line
  line `(5) For the purposes of this section, "reporting entity" means any intermediary or any authority or of`
  line `the Central or the State Government or any other person as may be notified in this behalf.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of sub-section (5), "intermediary" shall have the same meaning as`
  line `assigned to it in clause (n) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Prevention of Money-Laundering`
  line `Act, 2002 (15 of 2003).]`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (32874)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Certain officers to assist in inquiry, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32874&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `^1[20. Certain officers to assist in inquiry, etc.--The following officers shall assist the authorities in`
  line `the enforcement of this Act, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) income-tax authorities appointed under sub-section (1) of section 117 of the Income-tax`
  line `Act, 1961 (43 of 1961);`
  line
  line `(b) officers of the Customs and Central Excise Departments;`
  line
  line `(c) officers appointed under sub-section (1) of section 5 of the Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic`
  line `Substances Act, 1985 (61 of 1985);`
  line
  line `(d) officers of the stock exchange recognised under section 4 of the Securities Contracts`
  line `(Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(e) officers of the Reserve Bank of India constituted under sub-section (1) of section 3 of the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(f) police;`
  line
  line `(g) officers of enforcement appointed under sub-section (1) of section 36 of the Foreign Exchange`
  line `Management Act, 1999 (40 of 1999);`
  line
  line `(h) officers of the Securities and Exchange Board of India established under section 3 of the`
  line `Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992);`
  line
  line `(i) officers of any other body corporate constituted or established under a Central or a State Act;`
  line and
  line
  line `(j) such other officers of the Central Government, State Government, local authorities or banking`
  line `companies as the Central Government may, by notification, specify, in this behalf.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (32875)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power to call for information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32875&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `^1[21. Power to call for information.--(1) The Initiating Officer or the Approving Authority or the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority shall have power to require any officer of the Central Government or State`
  line `Government or a local body or any person or officer who is responsible for registering and maintaining`
  line `books of account or other documents containing a record of any transaction relating to any property or`
  line `any other person to furnish any information in relation to any person, point or matter as in his opinion`
  line `shall be useful for or relevant for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to sub-section (1), every officer or person referred to in sub-section (1) shall`
  line `furnish such information to any authority under this Act in such form and manner as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (32876)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Power of authority to impound documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32876&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `^1[22. Power of authority to impound documents.--(1) Where any books of account or other`
  line `documents are produced before the authority in any proceedings under this Act and the authority in this`
  line `behalf has reason to believe that any of the books of account or other documents are required to be`
  line `impounded and retained for any inquiry under this Act, it may impound and retain the books of account or`
  line `other documents for a period not exceeding three months from the date of order of attachment made by`
  line `the Adjudicating Authority under sub-section (3) of section 26:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period for retention of the books of account or other documents may be extended`
  line `beyond a period exceeding three months from the date of order of attachment made by the Adjudicating`
  line `Authority under sub-section (3) of section 26 where the authority records in writing the reasons for`
  line `extending the same.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the authority impounding and retaining the books of account or other documents, under`
  line `sub-section (1) is the Initiating Officer, he shall obtain approval of the Approving Authority within a`
  line `period of fifteen days from the date of initial impounding and seek further approval of the Approving`
  line `Authority for extending the period of initial retention, before the expiry of the period of initial retention, if`
  line `so required.`
  line
  line `(3) The period of retention of the books of account or other documents under sub-section (1) shall in`
  line `no case exceed a period of thirty days from the date of conclusion of all the proceedings under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The person, from whom the books of account or other documents were impounded under`
  line `sub-section (1), shall be entitled to obtain copies thereof.`
  line
  line `(5) On the expiry of the period specified under sub-section (1), the books of account or other`
  line `documents shall be returned to the person from whom such books of account or other documents were`
  line `impounded unless the Approving Authority or the Adjudicating Authority permits their release to any`
  line `other person.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (32877)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power of authority to conduct inquiry, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 173 (w.e.f. 1-11-2016)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32877&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The Initiating Officer, after obtaining prior`
  line `approval of the Approving Authority, shall have power to conduct or cause to be conducted any inquiry or`
  line `investigation in respect of any person, place, property, assets, documents, books of account or other`
  line `documents, in respect of any other relevant matters under this Act.`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that nothing contained in this section`
  line `shall apply and shall be deemed to have ever applied where a notice under sub-section (1) of section 24 has`
  line `been issued by the Initiating Officer.]`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (32878)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Notice and attachment of property involved in benami transaction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32878&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Initiating`
  line `Officer, on the basis of material in his possession, has reason to believe that any person is a benamidar in`
  line `respect of a property, he may, after recording reasons in writing, issue a notice to the person to show`
  line `cause within such time as may be specified in the notice why the property should not be treated as benami`
  line property.
  line
  line `^1[(2A) The benamidar, to whom a notice has been issued under sub-section (1), or the beneficial owner to whom a copy of such notice has been issued under sub-section (2), shall furnish the explanation or submissions, if any, within the period specified in the said notice or such period as may be extended by the Initiating Officer, not exceeding three months from the end of the month in which the said notice is issued.]`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Initiating Officer is of the opinion that the person in possession of the property held benami may alienate the property during the period specified in the notice, he may, with the previous approval of the Approving Authority, by order in writing, attach provisionally the property in the manner as may be prescribed, for a period not exceeding ^2[four months] ^3[from the last day of the month in which the notice under sub-section (1) is issued.]`
  line
  line `(4) The Initiating Officer, after making such inquires and calling for such reports or evidence as he deems fit and taking into account all relevant materials, shall, within a period of ^5[four months] ^6[from the last day of the month in which the notice under sub-section (1) is issued],--`
  line
  line `(a) where the provisional attachment has been made under sub-section (3),--`
  line
  line `(i) pass an order continuing the provisional attachment of the property with the prior approval of the Approving Authority, till the passing of the order by the Adjudicating Authority under subsection (3) of section 26; or`
  line
  line `(ii) revoke the provisional attachment of the property with the prior approval of the Approving Authority;`
  line
  line `(b) where provisional attachment has not been made under sub-section (3),--`
  line
  line `(i) pass an order provisionally attaching the property with the prior approval of the Approving`
  line `Authority, till the passing of the order by the Adjudicating Authority under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 26; or`
  line
  line `(ii) decide not to attach the property as specified in the notice, with the prior approval of the`
  line `Approving Authority.`
  line
  line `^7[Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, in computing the period of limitation, the period during which the proceeding is stayed by an order or injunction of any court shall be excluded:`
  line
  line `Provided that where immediately after the exclusion of the aforesaid period, the period of limitation referred to in sub-section (4) available to the Initiating Officer for passing order of attachment is less than thirty days, such remaining period shall be deemed to be extended to thirty days:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where immediately after the exclusion of the aforesaid period, the period of limitation referred to in sub-section (5) available to the Initiating Officer to refer the order of attachment to Adjudicating Authority is less than seven days, such remaining period shall be deemed to be extended to seven days.]`
  line
  line `(5) Where the Initiating Officer passes an order continuing the provisional attachment of the property under sub-clause (i) of clause (a) of sub-section (4) or passes an order provisionally attaching the property under sub-clause (i) of clause (b) of that sub-section, he shall, within fifteen days from the date of the attachment, draw up a statement of the case and refer it to the Adjudicating Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 158 (w.e.f. 1-10-2024).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 158, ibid., for "ninety days" (w.e.f. 1-10-2024).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 174, for "from the date of issue of notice under sub-section (1)" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 158, for "ninety days" (w.e.f. 1-10-2024).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 174, for "from the date of issue of notice under sub-section (1)" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by s. 174, ibid (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (32879)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Manner of service of notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32879&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `^1[25. Manner of service of notice.--(1) A notice under sub-section (1) of section 24 may be served on`
  line `the person named therein either by post or as if it were a summons issued by a Court under the Code of`
  line `Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
  line
  line `(2) Any notice referred to in sub-section (1) may be addressed--`
  line
  line `(i) in case of an individual, to such individual;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of a firm, to the managing partner or the manager of the firm;`
  line
  line `(iii) in the case of a Hindu undivided family, to Karta or any member of such family;`
  line
  line `(iv) in the case of a company, to the principal officer thereof;`
  line
  line `(v) in the case of any other association or body of individuals, to the principal officer or any`
  line `member thereof;`
  line
  line `(vi) in the case of any other person (not being an individual), to the person who manages or`
  line `controls his affairs.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (32880)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Adjudication of benami property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32880&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of a reference under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 24, the Adjudicating Authority shall issue notice, to furnish such documents, particulars or`
  line `evidence as is considered necessary on a date to be specified therein, on the following persons, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the person specified as a benamidar therein;`
  line
  line `(b) any person referred to as the beneficial owner therein or identified as such;`
  line
  line `(c) any interested party, including a banking company;`
  line
  line `(d) any person who has made a claim in respect of the property:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Adjudicating Authority shall issue notice within a period of thirty days from the`
  line `date on which a reference has been received:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the notice shall provide a period of not less than thirty days to the person to`
  line `whom the notice is issued to furnish the information sought.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the property is held jointly by more than one person, the Adjudicating Authority shall`
  line `make all endeavours to serve notice to all persons holding the property:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the notice is served on anyone of the persons, the service of notice shall not be`
  line `invalid on the ground that the said notice was not served to all the persons holding the property.`
  line
  line `(3) The Adjudicating Authority shall, after--`
  line
  line `(a) considering the reply, if any, to the notice issued under sub-section (1);`
  line
  line `(b) making or causing to be made such inquiries and calling for such reports or evidence as it`
  line `deems fit; and`
  line
  line `(c) taking into account all relevant materials,`
  line
  line `provide an opportunity of being heard to the person specified as a benamidar therein, the Initiating`
  line `Officer, and any other person who claims to be the owner of the property, and, thereafter, pass an order--`
  line
  line `(i) holding the property not to be a benami property and revoking the attachment order; or`
  line
  line `(ii) holding the property to be a benami property and confirming the attachment order, in all`
  line `other cases.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the Adjudicating Authority is satisfied that some part of the properties in respect of which`
  line `reference has been made to him is benami property, but is not able to specifically identify such part, he`
  line `shall record a finding to the best of his judgment as to which part of the properties is held benami.`
  line
  line `(5) Where in the course of proceedings before it, the Adjudicating Authority has reason to believe that`
  line `a property, other than a property referred to it by the Initiating Officer is benami property, it shall`
  line `provisionally attach the property and the property shall be deemed to be a property referred to it on the`
  line `date of receipt of the reference under sub-section (5) of section 24.`
  line
  line `(6) The Adjudicating Authority may, at any stage of the proceedings, either on the application of any`
  line `party, or suo motu, strike out the name of any party improperly joined or add the name of any person`
  line `whose presence before the Adjudicating Authority may be necessary to enable him to adjudicate upon and`
  line `settle all the questions involved in the reference.`
  line
  line `(7) No order under sub-section (3) shall be passed after the expiry of one year from the end of the`
  line `month in which the reference under sub-section (5) of section 24 was received.`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, in computing the period of limitation, the period`
  line `during which the proceeding is stayed by an order or injunction of any court shall be excluded:`
  line
  line `Provided that where immediately after the exclusion of the aforesaid period, the period of limitation`
  line `available to the Adjudicating Authority for passing order is less than sixty days, such remaining period shall`
  line `be deemed to be extended to sixty days.]`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that where the time limit for passing order under this sub-section expires during the period`
  line `beginning from the 1st day of July, 2021 and ending on the 29th day of September, 2021, the time limit for`
  line `passing such order shall be extended to the 30th day of September, 2021.]`
  line
  line `(8) The benamidar or any other person who claims to be the owner of the property may either appear`
  line `in person or take the assistance of an authorised representative of his choice to present his case.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of sub-section (8), authorised representative means a person`
  line `authorised in writing, being--`
  line
  line `(i) a person related to the benamidar or such other person in any manner, or a person regularly`
  line `employed by the benamidar or such other person as the case may be; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any officer of a scheduled bank with which the benamidar or such other person maintains an`
  line `account or has other regular dealings; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any legal practitioner who is entitled to practice in any civil court in India; or`
  line
  line `(iv) any person who has passed any accountancy examination recognised in this behalf by the Board;`
  line or
  line
  line `(v) any person who has acquired such educational qualifications as the Board may prescribe for this`
  line purpose.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 175 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 157 (w.e.f. 1-7-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (32881)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Confiscation and vesting of benami property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32881&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `^1[27. Confiscation and vesting of benami property.--(1) Where an order is passed in respect of any`
  line `property under sub-section (3) of section 26 holding such property to be a benami property, the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority shall, after giving an opportunity of being heard to the person concerned, make an`
  line `order confiscating the property held to be a benami property:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an appeal has been filed against the order of the Adjudicating Authority, the`
  line `confiscation of property shall be made subject to the order passed by the Appellate Tribunal under`
  line `section 46:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the confiscation of the property shall be made in accordance with such`
  line `procedure as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall apply to a property held or acquired by a person from the`
  line `benamidar for adequate consideration, prior to the issue of notice under sub-section (1) of section 24`
  line `without his having knowledge of the benami transaction.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an order of confiscation has been made under sub-section (1), all the rights and title in such`
  line `property shall vest absolutely in the Central Government free of all encumbrances and no compensation`
  line `shall be payable in respect of such confiscation.`
  line
  line `(4) Any right of any third person created in such property with a view to defeat the purposes of this`
  line `Act shall be null and void.`
  line
  line `(5) Where no order of confiscation is made upon the proceedings under this Act attaining finality, no`
  line `claim shall lie against the Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (32882)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Management of properties confiscated.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32882&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `^1[28. Management of properties confiscated.--(1) The Administrator shall have the power to receive`
  line `and manage the property, in relation to which an order of confiscation under sub-section (1) of section 27`
  line `has been made, in such manner and subject to such conditions, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, notify as many of its`
  line `officers as it thinks fit, to perform the functions of Administrators.`
  line
  line `(3) The Administrator shall also take such measures, as the Central Government may direct, to`
  line `dispose of the property which is vested in the Central Government under sub-section (3) of section 27, in`
  line `such manner and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (32883)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Possession of the property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32883&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `^1[29. Possession of the property.--(1) Where an order of confiscation in respect of a property under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 27, has been made, the Administrator shall proceed to take the possession of the`
  line property.
  line
  line `(2) The Administrator shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) by notice in writing, order within seven days of the date of the service of notice to any person,`
  line `who may be in possession of the benami property, to surrender or deliver possession thereof to the`
  line `Administrator or any other person duly authorised in writing by him in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(b) in the event of non-compliance of the order referred to in clause (a), or if in his opinion,`
  line `taking over of immediate possession is warranted, for the purpose of forcibly taking over possession,`
  line `requisition the service of any police officer to assist him and it shall be the duty of the officer to`
  line `comply with the requisition.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (32884)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Establishment of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 176, for "the Adjudicating Authority" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32884&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall, by notification, establish`
  line `an Appellate Tribunal to hear appeals against the orders of ^1[any authority] under thisAct.`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (32885)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Composition, etc., of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32885&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `^1[31. Composition etc., of Appellate Tribunal.--(1) The Appellate Tribunal shall consist of a`
  line `Chairperson and at least two other Members of which one shall be a Judicial Member and other shall be`
  line `an Administrative Member.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) the jurisdiction of the Appellate Tribunal may be exercised by Benches thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) a Bench may be constituted by the Chairperson with two Members as the Chairperson may`
  line `deem fit;`
  line
  line `(c) the Benches of the Appellate Tribunal shall ordinarily sit in the National Capital Territory of`
  line `Delhi and at such other places as the Central Government may, in consultation with the Chairperson,`
  line `by notification, specify;`
  line
  line `(d) the Central Government shall, by notification, specify the areas in relation to which each`
  line `Bench of the Appellate Tribunal may exercise its jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the Chairperson may transfer a Member`
  line `from one Bench to another Bench.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (32886)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Qualifications for appointment of Chairperson and Members of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32886&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `^1[32. Qualifications for appointment of Chairperson and Members of Appellate Tribunal.--(1) A`
  line `person shall not be qualified for appointment as Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal unless he is a`
  line `sitting or retired Judge of a High Court, who has completed not less than five years' of service.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a Member unless he--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a Judicial Member, has been a Member of the Indian Legal Service and has held`
  line `the post of Additional Secretary or equivalent post in that Service;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an Administrative Member, has been a Member of the Indian Revenue Service`
  line `and has held the post of Chief Commissioner of Income tax or equivalent post in that Service.`
  line
  line `(3) No sitting Judge of a High Court shall be appointed under this section except after consultation`
  line `with the Chief Justice of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairperson or a Member holding a post as such in any other Tribunal, established under any`
  line `law for the time being in force, in addition to his being the Chairperson or a Member of that Tribunal,`
  line `may be appointed as the Chairperson or a Member, as the case may be, of the Appellate Tribunal under`
  line `this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (32887)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Terms and conditions of services of Chairperson and Members of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32887&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `^1[33. Terms and conditions of services of Chairperson and Members of Appellate Tribunal.--(1)`
  line `The salary and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of the Chairperson`
  line `and other Members shall be such as may be prescribed and shall not be varied to their disadvantage`
  line `during their tenure.`
  line
  line `(2) Any vacancy caused to the office of the Chairperson or any other Member shall be filled up within`
  line `a period of three months from the date on which such vacancy occurs.]`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (32888)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Term of office of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32888&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `^1[34. Term of office of Chairperson and Members.--The Chairperson and Members of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal shall hold office for a term not exceeding five years from the date on which they enter upon their`
  line `office, or until they attain the age of sixty-five years, whichever is earlier and shall not be eligible for`
  line reappointment.]
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (32889)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Removal of Chairperson and Member from office in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32889&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `^1[35. Removal of Chairperson and Member from office in certain circumstances.--(1) The Central`
  line `Government may, in consultation with the Chief Justice of High Court, remove from office of the`
  line `Chairperson or any Member, who--`
  line
  line `(a) has been adjudged as an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government involves`
  line `moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(c) has become physically or mentally incapable; or`
  line
  line `(d) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions; or`
  line
  line `(e) has so abused his position as to render his continuance in office prejudicial to the public`
  line interest.
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson or Judicial Member shall not be removed from his office except by an order`
  line `made by the Central Government after an inquiry made by Chief Justice of the High Court in which the`
  line `Chairperson or Judicial Member has been informed of the charges against him and given a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard in respect of those charges.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may suspend from office the Chairperson or Judicial Member in respect`
  line `of whom a reference of conducting an inquiry has been made to the Chief Justice of the High Court under`
  line `sub-section (2), until the Central Government passes an order on receipt of the report of inquiry made by`
  line `Chief Justice of the High Court on the reference.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may regulate the procedure for inquiry referred to in sub-section (2) in`
  line `the manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The Administrative Member may be removed from his office by an order of the Central`
  line `Government on the grounds specified in sub-section (1) and in accordance with the procedure notified by`
  line `the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Administrative Member shall not be removed unless he has been given an`
  line `opportunity of being heard in the matter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (32890)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Vacancies etc., not to invalidate proceedings of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32890&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `^1[36. Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of Appellate Tribunal.--No act or proceeding of`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal shall be invalid merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of the Tribunal; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a Member of the Tribunal; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Tribunal not affecting the merits of the case.]`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (32891)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Resignation and removal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32891&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `^1[37. Resignation and removal.--The Chairperson or any other Member may, by notice in writing`
  line `under his hand addressed to the Central Government, resign his office:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson or any other Member shall, unless he is permitted by the Central`
  line `Government to relinquish his office sooner, continue to hold office until the expiry of three months from`
  line `the date of receipt of the notice or until a person duly appointed as his successor enters upon his office or`
  line `until the expiry of his term of office, whichever is earlier.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (32892)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Member to act as Chairperson in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32892&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `^1[38. Member to act as Chairperson in certain circumstances.--(1) In the event of the occurrence of`
  line `any vacancy in the office of the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal by reason of his death, resignation`
  line `or otherwise, the senior-most Member shall act as the Chairperson until the date on which a new`
  line `Chairperson, appointed in accordance with the provisions of this Act to fill such vacancy, enters upon his`
  line office.
  line
  line `(2) When the Chairperson is unable to discharge his functions owing to absence, illness or any other`
  line `cause, the senior-most Member shall discharge the functions of the Chairperson until the date on which`
  line `the Chairperson resumes his duties.]`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (32893)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Staff of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32893&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `^1[39. Staff of Appellate Tribunal.--(1) The Central Government shall provide the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `with such officers and employees as it may thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The officers and employees of the Appellate Tribunal shall discharge their functions under the`
  line `general superintendence of the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(3) The salaries and allowances and other conditions of service of the officers and employees of the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal shall be such, as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (32894)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Procedure and powers of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32894&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `^1[40. Procedure and powers of Appellate Tribunal.--(1) The Appellate Tribunal shall not be bound`
  line `by the procedure laid down by the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), but shall be guided by the`
  line `principles of natural justice and, subject to the other provisions of this Act, the Appellate Tribunal shall`
  line `have powers to regulate its own procedure.`
  line
  line `(2) The Appellate Tribunal shall, for the purposes of discharging its functions under this Act, have the`
  line `same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) while`
  line `trying a suit, in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) subject to the provisions of sections 123 and 124 of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872`
  line `(1 of 1872), requisitioning any public record or document or copy of such record or document from`
  line `any office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(f) reviewing its decisions;`
  line
  line `(g) dismissing a representation for default or deciding it ex parte;`
  line
  line `(h) setting aside any order of dismissal of any representation for default or any order passed by it`
  line `ex parte; and`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter, which may be, prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) An order made by the Appellate Tribunal under this Act shall be executable by it as a decree of`
  line `civil court and, for this purpose, the Appellate Tribunal shall have all the powers of a civil court.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (3), the Appellate Tribunal may transmit any`
  line `order made by it to a civil court having jurisdiction and the civil court shall execute the order as if it were`
  line `a decree made by that court.`
  line
  line `(5) All proceedings before the Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be judicial proceedings within`
  line `the meaning of sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `shall be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of sections 345 and 346 of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).]`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (32895)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Distribution of business amongst Benches of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32895&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `^1[41. Distribution of business amongst Benches of Appellate Tribunal.--Where any Benches are`
  line `constituted, the Chairperson may, from time to time, by notification, make provision as to the distribution`
  line `of the business of the Appellate Tribunal amongst the Benches and also provide for the matters which`
  line `may be dealt with by each Bench.]`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (32896)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Power of Chairperson of Appellate Tribunal to transfer cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32896&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `^1[42. Power of Chairperson of Appellate Tribunal to transfer cases.--On the application of any of`
  line `the parties and notice to the parties, and after hearing them, or on his own motion without any notice, the`
  line `Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal may transfer any case pending before one Bench, for disposal, to`
  line `any other Bench.]`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (32897)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Decision to be by majority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32897&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `^1[43. Decision to be by majority.--If the Members of a Bench consisting of two Members differ in`
  line `opinion on any point, they shall state the point or points on which they differ, and make a reference to the`
  line `Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal who shall either hear the point or points himself or refer the case`
  line `for hearing on the point or points by one or more of the other Members and the point or points shall be`
  line `decided according to the opinion of the majority of the Members of the Appellate Tribunal who have`
  line `heard the case, including those who first heard it.]`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (32898)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Members, etc., to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32898&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `^1[44. Members, etc., to be public servants.--The Chairperson, Members and other officers and`
  line `employees of the Appellate Tribunal, the Adjudicating Authority, Approving Authority, Initiating Officer,`
  line `Administrator and the officers subordinate to all of them shall be deemed to be public servants within the`
  line `meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).]`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (32899)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Bar of jurisdiction of civil courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32899&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `^1[45. Bar of jurisdiction of civil courts--No civil court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any suit or`
  line `proceeding in respect of any matter which any of the authorities, an Adjudicating Authority or the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal is empowered by or under this Act to determine, and no injunction shall be granted by`
  line `any court or other forum in respect of any action taken or to be taken in pursuance of any power conferred`
  line `by or under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (32900)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Appeals to Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32900&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person, including the Initiating Officer, aggrieved by`
  line `an order of the Adjudicating Authority may prefer an appeal in such form and along with such fees, as may`
  line `be prescribed, to the Appellate Tribunal against the order passed by the Adjudicating Authority under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 26, within a period of forty-five days from the date ^1[on which such order is`
  line `received by the Initiating Officer or received by such person.]`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) Any person aggrieved by an order passed by the authority under section 54A may prefer an`
  line `appeal in such form along with such fees, as may be prescribed, to the Appellate Tribunal against the said`
  line `order within a period of forty-five days from the date ^3[on which such order is received by such person.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Appellate Tribunal may entertain any appeal after the said period of forty-five days, if it is`
  line `satisfied that the appellant was prevented, by sufficient cause, from filing the appeal in time.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of an appeal under sub-section (1), ^4[or sub-section (1A)] the Appellate Tribunal may,`
  line `after giving the parties to the appeal an opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it thinks`
  line fit.
  line
  line `(4) An Appellate Tribunal while deciding the appeal shall have the power--`
  line
  line `(a) to determine a case finally, where the evidence on record issufficient;`
  line
  line `(b) to take additional evidence or to require any evidence to be taken by the Adjudicating`
  line `Authority, where the Adjudicating Authority has refused to admit evidence, which ought to have been`
  line admitted;
  line
  line `(c) to require any document to be produced or any witness to be examined for the purposes of`
  line `proceeding before it;`
  line
  line `(d) to frame issues which appear to the Appellate Tribunal essential for adjudication of the case`
  line `and refer them to the Adjudicating Authority for determination;`
  line
  line `(e) to pass final order and affirm, vary or reverse an order of adjudication passed by the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority and pass such other order or orders as may be necessary to meet the ends of`
  line justice.
  line
  line `(5) The Appellate Tribunal, as far as possible, may hear and finally decide the appeal within a period`
  line `of one year from the last date of the month in which the appeal isfiled.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 2023, s. 171, for "of the order" (w.e.f. 1-4-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 177 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 8 of 2023, s. 171, for "of that order" (w.e.f. 1-4-2023).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s.178, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (32901)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Rectification of mistakes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s.178, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-9-2019)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32901&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The Appellate Tribunal or any authority may, in order to rectify`
  line `any mistake apparent on the face of the record, amend any order passed by it under the provisions of this`
  line `Act, within a period of one year from the end of the month in which such order was passed.]`
  line
  line `(2) No amendment shall be made under sub-section (1), if the amendment is likely to affect any person`
  line `prejudicially, unless he has been given notice of intention to do so and has been given an opportunity of`
  line `being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (32902)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Right to representation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32902&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `^1[48. Right to representation.--(1) A person preferring an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal under this`
  line `Act may either appear in person or take the assistance of an authorised representative of his choice to`
  line `present his case before the Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may authorise one or more of its officers to act as presenting officers on`
  line `its behalf, and every person so authorised may present the case with respect to any appeal before the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "authorised representative" means a person authorised`
  line `by the appellant in writing to appear on his behalf, being--`
  line
  line `(i) a person related to the appellant in any manner, or a person regularly employed by the`
  line `appellant; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any officer of a scheduled bank with which the appellant maintains an account or has other`
  line `regular dealings; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any legal practitioner who is entitled to practice in any civil court in India; or`
  line
  line `(iv) any person who has passed any accountancy examination recognised in this behalf by the`
  line `Board; or`
  line
  line `(v) any person who has acquired such educational qualifications as the Board may prescribe for`
  line `this purpose.]`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (32903)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Appeal to High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32903&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `^1[49. Appeal to High Court.--(1) Any party aggrieved by any decision or order of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal may file an appeal to the High Court within a period of sixty days from the date of`
  line `communication of the decision or order of the Appellate Tribunal to him on any question of law arising`
  line `out of such order.`
  line
  line `(2) The High Court may entertain any appeal after the said period of sixty days, if it is satisfied that`
  line `the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the appeal within the period specified in`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Where the High Court is satisfied that a substantial question of law is involved in any case, it shall`
  line `formulate that question.`
  line
  line `(4) The appeal shall be heard only on the question so formulated, and the respondents shall, at the`
  line `hearing of the appeal, be allowed to argue that the case does not involve such question.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in this sub-section shall be deemed to take away or abridge the power of the court to hear,`
  line `for reasons to be recorded, the appeal on any other substantial question of law not formulated by it, if it is`
  line `satisfied that the case involves such question.`
  line
  line `(6) The High Court shall decide the question of law so formulated and deliver the judgment thereon`
  line `containing the grounds on which any decision is founded and may award any cost as it deems fit.`
  line
  line `(7) The High Court may determine any issue which--`
  line
  line `(a) has not been determined by the Appellate Tribunal; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been wrongly determined by the Appellate Tribunal, by reason of a decision on such`
  line `question of law as is referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(8) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908`
  line `(5 of 1908), relating to appeals to the High Court shall, as far as may be, apply in the case of appeals`
  line `under this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (32904)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32904&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `^1[50. Special Courts.--(1) The Central Government, in consultation with the Chief Justice of the High`
  line `Court, shall, for trial of an offence punishable under this Act, by notification, designate one or more`
  line `Courts of Session as Special Court or Special Courts for such area or areas or for such case or class or`
  line `group of cases as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) While trying an offence under this Act, a Special Court shall also try an offence other than an`
  line `offence referred to in sub-section (1), with which the accused may, under the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), be charged at the same trial.`
  line
  line `(3) The Special Court shall not take cognizance of any offence punishable under this Act except upon`
  line `a complaint in writing made by--`
  line
  line `(i) the authority; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any officer of the Central Government or State Government authorised in writing by that`
  line `Government by a general or special order made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(4) Every trial under this section shall be conducted as expeditiously as possible and every endeavour`
  line `shall be made by the Special Court to conclude the trial within six months from the date of filing of the`
  line complaint.]
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (32905)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Application of Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 to proceedings before Special Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32905&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `^1[51. Application of Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 to proceedings before Special Court.--(1)`
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974), shall apply to the proceedings before a Special Court and the persons conducting the`
  line `prosecution before the Special Court, shall be deemed to be Public Prosecutors:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may also appoint for any case or class or group of cases, a`
  line `Special Public Prosecutor.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall not be qualified to be appointed as a Public Prosecutor or a Special Public`
  line `Prosecutor under this section unless, the Public Prosecutor has been in practice as an advocate for not less`
  line `than seven years, and the Special Public Prosecutor has been in practice as an advocate for not less than`
  line `ten years in any court.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person appointed as a Public Prosecutor or a Special Public Prosecutor under this section`
  line `shall be deemed to be a Public Prosecutor within the meaning of clause (u) of section 2 of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) and the provisions of that Code shall have effect accordingly.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (32906)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Appeal and revision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32906&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `^1[52. Appeal and revision.--The High Court may exercise, so far as may be applicable, all the powers`
  line `conferred by Chapter XXIX or Chapter XXX of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), on a`
  line `High Court, as if a Special Court within the local limits of the jurisdiction of the High Court were a Court`
  line `of Session trying cases within the local limits of the jurisdiction of the High Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (32907)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Penalty for benami transaction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32907&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `^1[53. Penalty for benami transaction.--(1) Where any person enters into a benami transaction in`
  line `order to defeat the provisions of any law or to avoid payment of statutory dues or to avoid payment to`
  line `creditors, the beneficial owner, benamidar and any other person who abets or induces any person to enter`
  line `into the benami transaction, shall be guilty of the offence of benami transaction.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever is found guilty of the offence of benami transaction referred to in sub-section (1) shall be`
  line `punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one year, but which may`
  line `extend to seven years and shall also be liable to fine which may extend to twenty-five per cent. of the fair`
  line `market value of the property.]`
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (32908)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Penalty for false information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32908&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `^1[54. Penalty for false information.--Any person who is required to furnish information under this`
  line `Act knowingly gives false information to any authority or furnishes any false document in any proceeding`
  line `under this Act, shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six`
  line `months but which may extend to five years and shall also be liable to fine which may extend to ten per`
  line `cent. of the fair market value of the property.]`
obj_root_law_sections_54_a:
  sectionId (50248)
  sectionNo 54A
  orderNo 55
  title `Penalty for failure to comply with notices or furnish information`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 179 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=50248&sectionno=54A&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_54_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[54A. Penalty for failure to comply with notices or furnish information.--(1) Any person who fails`
  line `to, --`
  line
  line `(i) comply with summons issued under sub-section (1) of section 19; or`
  line
  line `(ii) furnish information as required under section 21, shall be liable to pay penalty of twenty-five`
  line `thousand rupees for each such failure.`
  line
  line `(2) The penalty under sub-section (1) shall be imposed by the authority who had issued the summons or`
  line `called for the information.`
  line
  line `(3) No order under sub-section (2) shall be passed by the authority unless the person on whom the`
  line `penalty is to be imposed has been given an opportunity of being heard:`
  line
  line `Provided that no penalty shall be imposed if, such person proves that there were good and sufficient`
  line `reasons which prevented him from complying with the summons or furnishing information.]`
obj_root_law_sections_54_b:
  sectionId (50249)
  sectionNo 54B
  orderNo 56
  title `Proof of entries in records or documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 179 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=50249&sectionno=54B&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_54_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[54B. Proof of entries in records or documents.--The entries in the records or other documents in the`
  line `custody of an authority shall be admitted in evidence in any proceedings for the prosecution of any person`
  line `for an offence under section 3 or this Chapter, as the case may be, and all such entries may be proved either`
  line by--
  line
  line `(i) the production of the records or other documents in the custody of the authority containing such`
  line `entries; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the production of a copy of the entries certified by the authority having custody of the records or`
  line `other documents under its signature stating that it is a true copy of the original entries and that such`
  line `original entries are contained in the records or other documents in its custody.]`
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (32909)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 57
  title `Previous sanction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32909&sectionno=55&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution shall be instituted against any person in respect of any offence under sections 3, 53 or section 54 without the previous sanction of the ^1[competent authority].]`
  line
  line `^2[Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "competent authority" means a Commissioner, a`
  line `Director, a Principal Commissioner of Income-tax or a Principal Director of Income-tax as defined in`
  line `clause (16), clause (21), clause (34B) and clause (34C), respectively, of section 2 of the Income-tax Act,`
  line `1961 (43 of 1961).]`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 180, for "Board" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 180, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_55_a:
  sectionId (92542)
  sectionNo 55A
  orderNo 58
  title `Power to tender Immunity from prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 158 (w.e.f. 1-10-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=92542&sectionno=55A&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_55_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[55A. Power to tender Immunity from prosecution.--(1) The Initiating Officer may, with a view to obtaining the evidence of the benamidar or any other person as referred to in section 53, other than the beneficial owner, tender immunity from prosecution for any offence under the said section to the benamidar or such other person, with the previous sanction of the competent authority as referred to in section 55, on the condition that the benamidar or such other person makes a full and true disclosure of the`
  line `whole circumstances relating to the benami transaction.`
  line
  line `(2) The tender of immunity made to, and accepted by, the benamidar or such other person, shall, to the extent to which the immunity extends, render him immune from prosecution for the offence in respect of which the tender was made and from the imposition of any penalty under section 53.`
  line
  line `(3) If it appears to the Initiating Officer that any person to whom immunity has been tendered under`
  line `this section has not complied with the conditions subject to which the tender was made, or is wilfully`
  line `concealing anything, or is giving false evidence, the Initiating Officer may record a finding to that effect,`
  line `and with the previous sanction of the competent authority as referred to in section 55, withdraw the`
  line `immunity tendered.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person against whom the immunity tendered is withdrawn in accordance with sub-section (3),`
  line `may be tried for the offence in respect of which the tender of immunity was made or for any other offence`
  line `of which he appears to have committed in connection with the same transaction and shall also be liable to`
  line `any penalty under this Act to which he would otherwise have been liable.]`
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (32910)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 59
  title `Repeal of provisions of certain Acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2016, s. 10, for sections 7 and 8 (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32910&sectionno=56&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `^1[56. Repeal of provisions of certain Acts.--(1) Sections 81, 82 and 94 of the Indian Trusts Act, 1882`
  line `(2 of 1882), section 66 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) and section 281A of the`
  line `Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961), are hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that nothing in sub-section (1) shall affect the`
  line `continued operation of section 281A of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961) in the State of Jammu and`
  line Kashmir.]
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (32911)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 60
  title `Certain transfers to be null and void.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2016, s. 10, for sections 7 and 8 (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32911&sectionno=57&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `^1[57. Certain transfers to be null and void.--Notwithstanding anything contained in the Transfer of`
  line `the Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882) or any other law for the time being in force, where, after the issue of a`
  line `notice under section 24, any property referred to in the said notice is transferred by any mode whatsoever,`
  line `the transfer shall, for the purposes of the proceedings under this Act, be ignored and if the property is`
  line `subsequently confiscated by the Central Government under section 27, then, the transfer of the property`
  line `shall be deemed to be null and void.]`
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (32912)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 61
  title Exemption.
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2016, s. 10, for sections 7 and 8 (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32912&sectionno=58&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `^1[58. Exemption.--(1) The Central Government may, by notification, exempt any property relating to`
  line `charitable or religious trusts from the operation of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification issued under sub-section (1) shall be laid before each House of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (32913)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 62
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2016, s. 10, for sections 7 and 8 (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32913&sectionno=59&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `^1[59. Power of Central Government to issue directions, etc.--(1) The Central Government may,`
  line `from time to time, issue such orders, instructions or directions to the authorities or require any person to`
  line `furnish information as it may deem fit for the proper administration of this Act and such authorities and`
  line `all other persons employed in execution of this Act shall observe and follow the orders, instructions and`
  line `directions of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) In issuing the directions or orders referred to in sub-section (1), the Central Government may have`
  line `regard to anyone or more of the following criteria, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) territorial area;`
  line
  line `(b) classes of persons;`
  line
  line `(c) classes of cases; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other criterion that may be specified by the Central Government in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) No orders, instructions or directions under sub-section (1) shall be issued so as to--`
  line
  line `(a) require any authority to decide a particular case in a particular manner; or`
  line
  line `(b) interfere with the discretion of the Adjudicating Authority in the discharge of its functions.]`
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (32914)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 63
  title `Application of other laws not barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2016, s. 10, for sections 7 and 8 (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32914&sectionno=60&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `^1[60. Application of other laws not barred.--The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and`
  line `not, save as hereinafter expressly provided, in derogation of any other law for the time being in force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (32915)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 64
  title `Offences to be non-cognizable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2016, s. 10, for sections 7 and 8 (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32915&sectionno=61&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `^1[61. Offences to be non-cognizable.--Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), an offence under this Act shall be non-cognizable.`
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (32916)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 65
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2016, s. 10, for sections 7 and 8 (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32916&sectionno=62&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `^1[62. Offences by companies.(1) Where a person committing contravention of any of the provisions`
  line `of this Act or of any rule, direction or order made thereunder is a company, every person who, at the time`
  line `the contravention was committed, was in charge of, and was responsible to, the company, for the conduct`
  line `of the business of the company as well as the company, shall be deemed to be guilty of the contravention`
  line `and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1), shall render any person liable to punishment if he proves`
  line `that the contravention took place without his knowledge.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where a contravention of any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or of any rule, direction or order made thereunder has been committed by a`
  line `company and it is proved that the contravention has taken place with the consent or connivance of, or is`
  line `attributable to any neglect on the part of any director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company,`
  line `the director, manager, secretary or other officer shal1 also be deemed to be guilty of the contravention and`
  line `shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means a body corporate, and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) a firm; and`
  line
  line `(ii) an association of persons or a body of individuals whether incorporated or not; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to--`
  line
  line `(i) a firm, means a partner in the firm;`
  line
  line `(ii) any association of persons or a body of individuals, means any member controlling the`
  line `affairs thereof.]`
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (32917)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 66
  title `Notice, etc., not to be invalid on certain grounds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2016, s. 10, for sections 7 and 8 (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32917&sectionno=63&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `^1[63. Notice, etc., not to be invalid on certain grounds.--No notice, summons, order, document or`
  line `other proceeding, furnished or made or issued or taken or purported to have been furnished or made or`
  line `issued or taken in pursuance of any of the provisions of this Act shall be invalid, or shall be deemed to be`
  line `invalid merely by reason of any mistake, defect or omission in the notice, summons, order, document or`
  line `other proceeding if the notice, summons, order, document or other proceeding is in substance and effect`
  line `in conformity with or according to the intent and purpose of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (32918)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 67
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2016, s. 10, for sections 7 and 8 (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32918&sectionno=64&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `^1[64. Protection of action taken in good faith.No prosecution, suit or other proceeding shall lie`
  line `against the Government or any officer of the Government or the Appellate Tribunal or the Adjudicating`
  line `Authority established under this Act, for anything done or intended to be done in good faith under this`
  line Act.]
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (32919)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 68
  title `Transfer of pending cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2016, s. 10, for sections 7 and 8 (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32919&sectionno=65&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `^1[65. Transfer of pending cases.--(1) Every suit or proceeding in respect of a benami transaction`
  line `pending in any Court (other than a High Court) or Tribunal or before any forum on the date of the`
  line `commencement of this Act shall stand transferred to the Adjudicating Authority or the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal, as the case may be, having jurisdiction in the matter.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any suit, or other proceeding stands transferred to the Adjudicating Authority or the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) the court, Tribunal or other forum shall, as soon as may be, after the transfer, forward the`
  line `records of the suit, or other proceeding to the Adjudicating Authority or the Appellate Tribunal, as the`
  line `case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) the Adjudicating Authority may, on receipt of the records, proceed to deal with the suit, or`
  line `other proceeding, so far as may be, in the same manner as in the case of a reference made under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 24, from the stage which was reached before the transfer or from any earlier`
  line `stage or de novo as the Adjudicating Authority may deem fit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (32920)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 69
  title `Proceedings, etc., against legal representative.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2016, s. 10, for sections 7 and 8 (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32920&sectionno=66&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `^1[66. Proceedings, etc., against legal representative.(1) Where a person dies during the course of`
  line `any proceeding under this Act, any proceeding taken against the deceased before his death shall be`
  line `deemed to have been taken against the legal representative and may be continued against the legal`
  line `representative from the stage at which it stood on the date of the death of the deceased.`
  line
  line `(2) Any proceeding which could have been taken against the deceased if he had survived may be`
  line `taken against the legal representative and all the provisions of this Act, except sub-section (2) of section 3`
  line `and the provisions of Chapter VII, shall apply accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any property of a person has been held benami under sub-section (3) of section 26, then, it`
  line `shall be lawful for the legal representative of the person to prefer an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal, in`
  line `place of the person and the provisions of section 46 shall, so far as may be, apply, or continue to apply, to`
  line `the appeal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (32921)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 70
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2016, s. 10, for sections 7 and 8 (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32921&sectionno=67&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `^1[67. Act to have overriding effect.--The provisions of this Act shall have effect, notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (32922)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 71
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32922&sectionno=68&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `^1[68. Power to make rules.--(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules for`
  line `carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) manner of ascertaining the fair market value under clause 16 of section 2;`
  line
  line ^2*****
  line
  line `(d) the powers and functions of the authorities under sub-section (2) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(e) other powers of the authorities under clause (f) of sub-section (1) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(f) the form and manner of furnishing any information to the authority under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 21;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner of provisional attachment of property under sub-section (3) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(h) the procedure for confiscation of benami property under the second proviso to sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 27;`
  line
  line `(i) the manner and conditions to receive and manage the property under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 28;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner and conditions of disposal of property vested in the Central Government under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(k) the salaries and allowances payable to and the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Chairperson and other Members of the Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (1) of section 33;`
  line
  line `(l) the manner of prescribing procedure for removal of Chairperson or Member under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(m) the salaries and allowances payable to and the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `officers and employees of the Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (3) of section 39;`
  line
  line `(n) any power of the Appellate Tribunal under clause (i) of sub-section (2) of section 40;`
  line
  line `(o) the form in which appeal shall be filed and the fee for filing the appeal under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 46;`
  line
  line `(p) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed, or in respect of which provision is to`
  line `be made, by rules.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2016, s. 10, for sections 7 and 8 (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Clauses (b) and (c) omitted by Act 13 of 2021, s. 158 (w.e.f. 1-7-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (32923)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 72
  title `Laying of rules and notifications before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2016, s. 10, for sections 7 and 8 (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32923&sectionno=69&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `^1[69. Laying of rules and notifications before Parliament.--Every rule made and notification issued`
  line `under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made or issued, before each House of Parliament,`
  line `while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or`
  line `more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rules or notifications,`
  line `as the case may be, both Houses agree that the rules or notifications, as the case may be, should not be`
  line `made or issued, the rule or notification, as the case may be, shall thereafter have effect only in such`
  line `modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or`
  line `notification, as the case may be.]`
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (32924)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 73
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2016, s. 10, for sections 7 and 8 (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32924&sectionno=70&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `^1[70. Power to remove difficulties.--(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to be necessary for removing the difficulty.`
  line
  line `(2) No order shall be made under this section after the expiry of two years from the commencement`
  line `of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (32925)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 74
  title `Transitional provision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2016, s. 10, for sections 7 and 8 (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32925&sectionno=71&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `^1[71. Transitional provision.--The Central Government may, by notification, provide that until the`
  line `Adjudicating Authorities are appointed and the Appellate Tribunal is established under this Act, the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority appointed under sub-section (1) of section 6 of the Money-Laundering Act, 2002`
  line `(15 of 2003) and the Appellate Tribunal established under section 25 of that Act may discharge the`
  line `functions of the Adjudicating Authority and Appellate Tribunal, respectively, under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (32926)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 75
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes `1. Section 9 renumbered as section 72 thereof by Act 43 of 2016, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369&sectionId=32926&sectionno=72&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00032_198845_1517807326369
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[72.] Repeal and saving.--(1) The Benami Transactions (Prohibition of the Right to Recover`
  line `Property) Ordinance, 1988 (Ord. 2 of 1988) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Ordinance shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
